{"article_id":"OLY7uV3SXTqODvK3","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Unemployment Rate Drops To 7.8 Percent ;","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"114,000 Jobs Added To Payrolls","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"The nation 's unemployment rate fell to 7.8 percent in September from 8.1 percent in August","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"even though just 114,000 jobs were added to private and public payrolls ,","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"the Bureau of Labor Statistics reports .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"Those hard-to-reconcile figures","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"- a decline in the jobless rate","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"even though job growth was relatively weak -","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"appear to be at least partly explained by a sharp increase in the number of Americans","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"who found part-time jobs","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"and counted themselves as employed .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"The decline in the jobless rate means that for the first time","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"since President Obama took the oath of office in January 2009 ,","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"unemployment is officially below 8 percent .","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"With jobs and the economy atop the list of issues","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"voters care most about ,","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"the report is sure to be a hot topic on the campaign trail .","depth":5},{"id":17,"text":"We 'll have more from the report , as well as reactions to it , shortly .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"As we said Thursday ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"this news is sure to be a hot topic on the campaign trail .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"At a campaign event in Fairfax , Va. , President Obama just said","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"that today 's report is a `` reminder","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"that this country has come too far","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"to turn back now . ''","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"Though there are `` still too many of our friends and neighbors ''","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"looking for work ,","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"Obama said ,","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"`` we are moving forward again . ''","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"Businesses ,","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"he said ,","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"`` have now added 5.2 million new jobs over the past 2 1/2 years ...","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"[ and ] the unemployment rate has fallen to its lowest level","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"since I took office . ''","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"Update at 10:25 a.m . ET .","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"Labor Secretary Says","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"Talk Of `` October Surprise '' Is `` Ludicrous . ''","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"We 've added this post :","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"Labor Secretary Says","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"Talk Of Fudged Jobless Numbers Is Insulting .","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"Update at 9:48 a.m . ET .","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"White House Says","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"News Is `` Further Evidence ''","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"That Economy Is On The Mend :","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"`` While there is more work","depth":14},{"id":44,"text":"that remains to be done ,","depth":14},{"id":45,"text":"today 's employment report provides further evidence","depth":14},{"id":46,"text":"that the U.S. economy is continuing to heal from the wounds","depth":15},{"id":47,"text":"inflicted by the worst downturn since the Great Depression , ''","depth":15},{"id":48,"text":"White House top economic adviser Alan Krueger writes .","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"Update at 9:45 a.m . ET .","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"Broader Unemployment Rate Stayed At 14.7 Percent :","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"The Wall Street Journal walks through how the `` U-6 '' unemployment rate remained unchanged last month at 14.7 percent .","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"That rate ,","depth":15},{"id":53,"text":"as the Journal says :","depth":15},{"id":54,"text":"`` Includes everyone in the official rate plus 'marginally attached workers '","depth":15},{"id":55,"text":"- those","depth":16},{"id":56,"text":"who are neither working nor looking for work ,","depth":17},{"id":57,"text":"but say","depth":18},{"id":58,"text":"they want a job","depth":19},{"id":59,"text":"and have looked for work recently ;","depth":19},{"id":60,"text":"and people","depth":14},{"id":61,"text":"who are employed part-time for economic reasons ,","depth":15},{"id":62,"text":"meaning they want full-time work","depth":17},{"id":63,"text":"but took a part-time schedule instead","depth":17},{"id":64,"text":"because that 's all","depth":17},{"id":65,"text":"they could find . ''","depth":17},{"id":66,"text":"Update at 9:30 a.m . ET .","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"Romney Says","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"This Is n't A `` Real Recovery . ''","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"This statement from Republican presidential nominee was just released by his campaign :","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"`` This is not what a real recovery looks like .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"We created fewer jobs in September than in August , and fewer jobs in August than in July ,","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"and we 've lost over 600,000 manufacturing jobs","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"since President Obama took office .","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"If not for all the people","depth":14},{"id":75,"text":"who have simply dropped out of the labor force ,","depth":14},{"id":76,"text":"the real unemployment rate would be closer to 11 % . ``","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"The results of President Obama 's failed policies are staggering","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"- 23 million Americans","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"struggling for work ,","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"nearly one in six","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"living in poverty","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"and 47 million people","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"dependent on food stamps","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"to feed themselves and their families .","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"The choice in this election is clear .","depth":5},{"id":86,"text":"Under President Obama , we 'll get another four years like the last four years .","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"If I 'm elected ,","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"we will have a real recovery with pro-growth policies","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"that will create 12 million new jobs and rising incomes for everyone . ''","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"Update at 9:15 a.m . ET .","depth":4},{"id":91,"text":"More On The Two Surveys :","depth":6},{"id":92,"text":"As we just explained ,","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"the unemployment rate is based on a `` household survey , ''","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"while the figure on job growth comes from a survey of employers .","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"The Financial Times notes","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"that :","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"`` The sampling error on the business establishment survey is plus or minus 100,000 jobs .","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"The sampling error on the household survey is plus or minus 280,000 jobs . ''","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"Update at 8:55 a.m . ET .","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"Two Surveys , Two Different Indicators :","depth":6},{"id":101,"text":"The unemployment rate","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"reported by BLS","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"is based on surveys","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"it does","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"of households .","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"Basically , researchers ask a series of questions","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"to determine who is and is n't working , what types of jobs they have ,","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"whether they 're actively looking for work , etc .","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"That survey produced an eye-popping number :","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"an estimated 873,000 more people reported being `` employed '' in September than in August .","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"Reuters says","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"that was the biggest one-month jump in that indicator since June 1983 .","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"The figure on payroll employment","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"- in this case , a gain of 114,000 jobs -","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"is based on a survey of public and private employers .","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"How could 873,000 more people be working","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"if only 114,000 jobs were added to payrolls ?","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"One reason :","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"582,000 more people said","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"they took part-time work `` for economic reasons '' last month .","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"Our colleagues at Planet Money have previously reported about how BLS puts its numbers together and the steps","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"it takes","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"to keep them secret .","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"Today , it adds a post on `` 5 Ways","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"Of Looking At Unemployment . ''","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"Update at 8:40 a.m . ET .","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"How Did The Jobless Rate Fall","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"If Job Growth Was Slow ?","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"An increase of 114,000 jobs in an economy with a labor force of more than 155 million people would n't alone account for a sharp drop in the jobless rate .","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"So why did the rate decline three tenths of a point ?","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"The Associated Press notes","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"that :","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"`` The economy also created 86,000 more jobs in July and August","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"than first estimated . ...","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"The revisions show","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"employers added 146,000 jobs per month from July through September , up from 67,000 in the previous three months . ''","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"The BLS report also says","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"there were 456,000 fewer people","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"counted as being among the unemployed","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"last month .","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"Update at 8:35 a.m . ET .","depth":7},{"id":142,"text":"First Time Below 8 Percent Since January 2009 :","depth":6},{"id":143,"text":"At 7.8 percent , the jobless rate is back","depth":8},{"id":144,"text":"where it was in January 2009","depth":8},{"id":145,"text":"and is below 8 percent for the first time","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"since President Obama was sworn in that month .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":293,"left":148,"right":292,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":148,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":292,"left":230,"right":291,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":230,"left":159,"right":229,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left":156,"right":158,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":156,"left":150,"right":155,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":149,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":155,"left":152,"right":154,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":152,"left":5,"right":151,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":8,"right":153,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":158,"left":157,"right":13,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":157,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":229,"left":161,"right":228,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":161,"left":160,"right":16,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":160,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":228,"left":163,"right":227,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":163,"left":17,"r